The paper discusses compressive sensing and its application to sparse signal recovery using cross validation. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the fundamental limits of data compression and communication, is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses statistical methods and algorithms, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.SP (Signal Processing). Additionally, the paper provides theoretical analysis and numerical experiments, which could place it in cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
